CatDescriptText: Margaret Lucas, housewife, Oakland and Janie Jeffries, housewife, McKees Rocks, were part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 5, 1960, pg. 29 with question: "Do you think voters will choose the Republican or the Democratic candidate for the presidency?"  Mrs. Lucas' answer reads: "I couldn't say but Nixon hasn't done too bad...He might become President."  Mrs. Jeffries' answer reads: "I think that Kennedy is going to be President."
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of Margaret Lucas wearing light colored coat and dark hat with bow, standing in front of Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown; Portrait of Janie Jeffries wearing eyeglasses and patterned head scarf, standing in front of Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
